===Definitions===
{{head|zh|hanzi}}

# {{lb|zh|literary}} [[Jupiter]] {{gloss|planet}}
#* {{zh-x|^昔 ^武王 伐 ^殷，^歲 在 ^鶉火，……^歲 之 所在，則 我 ^有周 之 分野 也，……|Formerly when {{w|King Wu of Zhou|King Wu}} attacked {{w|Shang dynasty|Yin}}, the '''Year Star / Jupiter''' was in Quail Fire, [...] The '''Year Star / Jupiter''' was in the [heavenly] region allotted to us, the {{w|Zhou dynasty|Youzhou}}, [...]|ref=Guoyu}}
# [[year]]
#* {{zh-x|子.曰：「歲 寒，然 後 知 松柏 之 後 彫[凋]{diāo} 也。」|The Master said, "When the '''year''' becomes cold, then we know how the pine and the cypress are the last to lose their leaves."|ref=Analects|CL}}
# {{w|Tai Sui}}, the [[god]] [[represent]]ing [[each]] of [[these]] [[year]]s
# {{lb|zh|literary}} [[age]]
# {{lb|zh|literary}} [[time]]; [[period]]
# {{lb|zh|literary}} [[crop]] [[harvest]]s of the [[year]]
#* {{zh-x|苟 無 歲，何 有 民？苟 無 民，何 有 君？|Whence the people, if not for '''the harvests'''? Whence the prince, if not for the people?|ref=Zhanguoce}}
# {{lb|zh|literary}} {{zh-classifier|time|t=[[year]]}}
# {{zh-classifier|age (of a person or animal)|t=[[year]] old}}
#: {{zh-x|你 現在 幾 歲？|How old are you now?}}
#: {{zh-x|我 十八 歲。|I am 18 '''years''' old.}}
#: {{zh-x|一個 十 歲 的 女孩|a ten-'''year'''-old girl}}

====Usage notes====
Ages in {{zh-l|歲}} are traditionally reckoned using the Chinese lunar calendar, considered as 1 year old at the moment of birth and increasing not during birthdays, but at the [[Chinese New Year]].

